parameters:
\n<Ameria>"You don't have to sound so reluctant. This is our home, you
know?"

\n<Lyric>"This isn't home for me, and as a demon, I can't feel
comfortable in a church. Being here gives me the creeps...
really creeps me out."

\n<Lyric>"Let's just move on quickly. If we don't figure out that
thief's deal, we'll have no choice but to head to Anatose,
right?"

\n<Ameria>"Alright, alright. Just wait here for a bit. There should be
some portable food in the storage, I'll go get it."

\n<Roselitte>"...Phew. You should rest your body a little too. If you
don't like the church, it's okay to stay outside. It won't
take long."
\n<Lyric>"That... thanks. For taking us along with you."

\n<Lyric>"Ameria seems happy because of you... um, how do I put it...
so, like, thanks? You know?"
\n<Roselitte>"Thanks?... I don't quite understand what you mean."

\n<Lyric>"Ever since she's been with you, she's been in a good mood.
Since you said it was okay for her to come along, I just
thought that was nice. That's all."
\n<Roselitte>"...Why do you think Ameria is so determined to follow me?"

\n<Lyric>"You saved her, didn't you? If that's the case, isn't that
reason enough? She's that kind of person."

\n<Roselitte>"I might be mistaken but... sometimes she looks sad. As if
she's burdened with thoughts or hiding something."
\n<Roselitte>"Do you have any idea what it could be?"
\n<Lyric>"...That. That's what I wanted to talk to you about."
Roselitte tilted her head slightly, urging him to continue.

\n<Lyric>"When I first met Ameria here, she was crying. She said 'I'm
sorry, Father'."
\n<Roselitte>"The priest is currently away on the mainland, correct?"

\n<Lyric>"Seems so. But I heard from the villagers in Annabern... The
priest won't be returning here for a while."

\n<Lyric>"I don't know. But maybe something serious happened because
of Ameria."

\n<Lyric>"...I thought you might know something about it, but it
seems like you don't have a clue either."

\n<Roselitte>"The control of regional affairs is delegated to the local
lords. Even if something did happen, the empire's territory
is vast, so I can't keep track of every minor incident."

\n<Roselitte>"But not returning to the mainland... Perhaps the matter is
more significant than I am aware of. Once I return, I should
investigate--"
\n<Roselitte>"...Was it okay for you to tell me this?"

\n<Lyric>"Ameria won't talk about it... No, maybe she can't talk
about it."

\n<Lyric>"But no matter what she does, I want to be by her side and
protect her."

\n<Lyric>"...But I'm a demon. A succubus. I can't always be by her
side. That's why I want to do something for her now."
\n<Lyric>"...But I don't know what I can do for her."

\n<Lyric>"Telling her to 'hang in there' or 'cheer up'... I don't
want to say such things to her when she's always trying hard
and staying cheerful."

\n<Lyric>"But since she won't talk about it, all I can do is offer
those words of encouragement."

\n<Lyric>"...Rose. If you were in my position, what could you do for
Ameria?"
\n<Roselitte>"...You really do care about Ameria, don't you?"

\n<Lyric>"Wha--! No, that's not it. I just find it annoying when she
looks down, so I'm saying it for that reason!"

\n<Lyric>"Grrr... Anyway, come on, hurry up and tell me your
thoughts."
After a moment of thought, Roselitte smiled.
\n<Roselitte>"There is a way. A good method to cheer up Ameria."
Roselitte gently placed her hand on Lyric's head.

\n<Roselitte>"When Ameria leans on you, she always seems truly happy and
smiles."

\n<Roselitte>"You are kind and think of her more than anyone else. And I
believe that she knows that better than anyone."

\n<Roselitte>"Having you by her side is probably the greatest comfort for
Ameria right now."

\n<Roselitte>"You don't need to think so hard about it. It's not about
being a demon and not being able to stay by her side, but
being there for her as a friend."
\n<Lyric>"...Can you let go of my hand...?"

\n<Roselitte>"Oh? But you said before that it was okay for me to stroke
it."
\n<Lyric>"I did say that! But stop it now!"
\n<Lyric>"That's why I said stop! I'll, I'll kill you!"
